headline: Housing Stocks Rally Despite Weak Jobs Report
summary: Chalk up Friday’s stock market sell-off to worries about tariffs and the weak jobs report.  Fears of an economic slowdown are on the rise, and some have even started to suggest that a recession could be in the cards.  With that in mind, it may seem a little odd that shares of companies with ties to the housing market were some of the market’s big winners.
